# Todo App

A command-line todo application with in-memory storage, built using Python.

## Features

- Add todo items with title and description
- List all todo items with status indicators
- Update existing todo items
- Delete todo items by ID
- Mark items as complete/incomplete
- All data stored in memory only (no persistence)

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.13+
- UV package manager

## Setup

1. Clone the repository
2. Navigate to the project directory
3. Install dependencies using UV: `uv sync`

## Usage

### Add a new todo:
```bash
python src/cli/main.py add --title "My Task" --description "Task details"
```

### List all todos:
```bash
python src/cli/main.py list
```

### Update a todo:
```bash
python src/cli/main.py update --id 1 --title "New Title"
```

### Mark complete:
```bash
python src/cli/main.py complete --id 1
```

### Mark incomplete:
```bash
python src/cli/main.py incomplete --id 1
```

### Delete a todo:
```bash
python src/cli/main.py delete --id 1
```

## Architecture

- **Models**: Handle data representation (`TodoItem`)
- **Services**: Handle business logic (`TodoService`)
- **CLI**: Handle user interaction (`main.py`)

## Development

All code follows clean architecture principles with separation of concerns between models, services, and CLI. In-memory storage only as required by specification.
